Sierra Suites Software - AWS POC Assessment - Page 4 of 11SECTION 2: THE AI INTELLIGENCE GAP2.1 Current State vs Required StateOur AI infrastructure is fully built with user interfaces, database tables, and API integrationlayers. However, the intelligence layer currently uses placeholder logic rather than machinelearning models trained on real construction data.Example: Smart Estimator ComparisonCurrent State (Demo):• Input: 2,500 sqft office renovation in San Francisco• Output: $412,500 - $465,000 (hardcoded range)• Basis: Generic multiplier logic• Confidence: 92% (static value)Required State (After POC):• Input: 2,500 sqft office renovation in San Francisco• Output: $438,200 - $487,600 (ML-predicted range)• Basis: Analysis of 127 similar projects from public datasets• Confidence: 89% (calculated from model certainty and data quality)• Similar Projects: Provides comparable project references with outcomes2.2 The 8 AI Features Requiring IntelligenceAI Tool Current State After POCSmart Estimator Hardcoded cost ranges ML-based cost prediction fromsimilar projectsProject Predictor Not embedded on projectpagesReal-time embedded analysison every projectMaterial Optimizer Generic savings percentages Data-driven cost savings andcarbon metricsSafety Sentinel Static risk scores Industry-calibrated riskprobabilities
Sierra Suites Software - AWS POC Assessment - Page 5 of 11SECTION 3: POC SCOPE & TECHNICAL APPROACH3.1 The 8 AI Tools - Detailed SpecificationsTool 1: Smart EstimatorPurpose: Provide accurate cost estimates for construction projects based on projectspecifications and historical data patterns.Input Parameters:• Project type (residential, commercial, industrial, infrastructure)• Square footage and number of floors• Location (city, state, zip code)• Quality level (economy, standard, premium, luxury)• Special requirements (LEED certification, seismic, historic preservation)Output Deliverables:• Cost range with confidence intervals• Breakdown by major categories (structure, MEP, finishes, site work)• Similar project comparisons• Regional cost adjustments• Confidence score based on data qualityML Approach:• Regression models for cost prediction• Similarity matching for comparable projects• Feature engineering for location and project attributes• Ensemble methods for improved accuracyTool 2: Project Predictor (Embedded on Project Pages)Purpose: Provide real-time project health analysis and risk predictions directly within theproject management interface.Integration Approach:• Embedded directly into /projects/[id] pages• Automatic data collection from project updates• Real-time analysis triggered by data changes• WebSocket connections for live updatesUI Components:• Project Health Score (0-100) with visual indicator• Risk Dashboard with top 3-5 risks• Predictive Timeline with confidence intervals• Recommendations Feed with actionable insights• Similar Projects Carousel for comparison• Alert System for critical issuesTool 3: Material OptimizerPurpose: Identify cost-saving opportunities and carbon footprint reduction through intelligentmaterial selection.Key Features:• Alternative material suggestions with cost comparisons• Carbon footprint calculations for each option• Bulk purchasing opportunities• Local supplier recommendations• Performance trade-off analysisTool 4: Safety Sentinel
Sierra Suites Software - AWS POC Assessment - Page 6 of 11Purpose: Predict and prevent safety incidents through risk analysis of work activities andsite conditions.Risk Assessment Factors:• Work type and activity hazards• Weather conditions and forecasts• Equipment and machinery involved• Worker experience and training levels• Historical incident patternsAdditional AI Features (5-8)5. Timeline Predictor: Milestone-by-milestone schedule forecasting with weather andresource considerations6. Change Order Predictor: Budget contingency recommendations based on projectcomplexity and historical patterns7. Carbon Footprint Estimator: Total project emissions calculation with reductionstrategies8. Total Risk Score: Comprehensive project health indicator combining all risk factors
Sierra Suites Software - AWS POC Assessment - Page 7 of 11SECTION 4: TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION4.1 Data StrategyThe POC will leverage publicly available construction datasets to train machine learningmodels. Data sources will be selected based on:• Relevance to construction industry patterns• Data quality and completeness• Geographic diversity for better generalization• Temporal relevance (recent data preferred)• Coverage of key project attributes4.2 AWS Services ArchitectureData Pipeline:• AWS Glue for ETL and data normalization• Amazon S3 for data lake storage• AWS Data Pipeline for orchestrationMachine Learning:• Amazon SageMaker for model training and deployment• SageMaker Feature Store for feature management• SageMaker Model Registry for version control• SageMaker Endpoints for real-time inferenceAPI & Integration:• API Gateway for RESTful endpoints• Lambda functions for business logic• ElastiCache for response caching• CloudWatch for monitoring and alerting4.3 Model Development Approach1. Data Collection & PreparationGather and clean public construction datasets, normalize formats, handle missingvalues2. Feature EngineeringExtract relevant features, create derived variables, encode categorical data3. Model TrainingTrain multiple model architectures, perform hyperparameter tuning, cross-validation4. Model EvaluationAssess accuracy metrics, validate against holdout data, ensure generalization5. Deployment & IntegrationDeploy models to SageMaker endpoints, integrate with Next.js frontend
